entries.arrived_at_loc: Stand by for next transmission to take place. Stay in this location until transmission is completed.
entries.attack_notify: pcontrast1 Tactical Computer:pcontrast3 <Warning! Enemy fighters incoming at attack speeds with weapons armed.>
entries.first_attack: You have been spotted. Be on the look out for enemy fighters.
entries.found_loc: Transmission point located. Travel to the location in your nav computer and stand by to intercept the transmission.
entries.mission_complete: Nice work, pilot. Stand by for delivery information.
entries.outofrange: Transmission signal lost. Return to transmission location.
entries.outofrange_failed: Transmission signal ended. Return to your superior officer to explain your failure to gather the information.
entries.quest_defendpoint_d: You must remain at that location until the signal is completed. If the Coynite notice you they will attack. Defend yourself but do not leave the area until the signal is completed.
entries.quest_location_d: The relay point is located inside of the Dathomir system.
entries.quest_reachpoint_d: Once you have reached the relay point, wait for the broadcast to begin.
entries.split_quest_alert: We need that data brought to one of our command vessels so we can decypher the message. Stand by for the navigation coordinates.
entries.title: Dathomir System: Intercept the Coynite Message
entries.title_d: The captured Coynite held out for as long as he could but eventually talked. Apparently the Coynite have an ally or allies from the prison on the planet's surface. They have been using communications satellites to broadcast instructions to the Coynite. You are to travel to one of the relay points and intercept these instructions.
entries.trans_update: Transmission Update: <%DI percent of message received.>
entries.transmission_received: Transmission Update: <Transmission received. Stand by for further instructions.>
entries.transmission_start: Transmission Update: <Transmission frequency located. Beginning download of encrypted message.>
